n the latter video. Chrysler used the instrumental and Eminem for their 2011 “Born of Fire” Super Bowl commercial. In 2021, Eminem opened up a restaurant in Detroit called “Mom’s Spaghetti”, which is a lyric that’s been meme’d extensively (even being given its own fan-made song. ) Expand      +927     3  7   Share    Q&A Find answers to frequently asked questions about the song and explore its deeper meaning Ask a question Has "Lose Yourself" reached any milestones?  Genius Answer 1 contributor As of February 28, 2018, “Lose Yourself” has reached Diamond (10x Multi-Platinum) certification by the RIAA.  Was the song ever performed by Eminem on the Oscars?  Genius Answer 1 contributor Though “Lose Yourself” was nominated and won for “Best Original Song” in 2002 at the Oscar’s, Eminem did not perform the song on stage that year. It wasn’t until 18 years later on February 9, 2020 where Eminem made a surprise appearance on the Oscar’s stage to perform the song there for the first time.       What makes the song important?  Genius Answer 2 contributors “Lose Yourself” was the first ever hip hop track to win an Oscar for Best Original Song.  Was the song ever performed on the Super Bowl halftime show?  Is this song featured on a movie?  Has the song ever been used for a US presidential campaign?  What lists has the song appeared on?  Translations  Official Instrumental  Who produced “Lose Yourself” by Eminem?  When did Eminem release “Lose Yourself”?  Who wrote “Lose Yourself” by Eminem?     The Vinyl LPs    (2015) Eminem 1. Public Service Announcement 2. My Name Is 3. Guilty Conscience 4. Brain Damage 5. Paul (Skit) 6. If I Had 7. ’97 Bonnie & Clyde 8. Bitch 9. Role Model 10. Lounge (Skit) 11. My Fault 12. Ken Kaniff (Skit) 13. Cum on Everybody 14. Rock Bottom 15. Just Don’t Give a Fuck 16. Soap (Skit) 17. As the World Turns 18. I’m Shady 19. Bad Meets Evil 20. Still Don’t Give a Fuck 21. Public Service Announcement 2000 22. Kill You 23. Stan 24. Paul (Skit) [2000] 25. Wh